    • Method Detail

      • getHtmlReplaceValue

        public String getHtmlReplaceValue(String modifierPrefix,
                                  UUID uuid)
        Description copied from class: PluginData
        Used to get the string for the html page. parseContainer(modifierPrefix, value); should be used for all return values so that div, icon, prefix and suffix are added. This method is used when AnalysisType.HTML is set, or while getting the value for the inspect page. When using AnalysisType.HTML a random UUID is given, so it should be disregarded. modifierPrefix is empty in that case.
        Specified by:
        getHtmlReplaceValue in class PluginData
        Parameters:
        modifierPrefix - Modifier determined by AnalysisType's modifier-variable.
        uuid - UUID of the player or random UUID if AnalysisType.HTML is used.
        Returns:
        html for the page.

      • getValue

        public Serializable getValue(UUID uuid)
        Description copied from class: PluginData
        Used to get the value for analysis. The return value is determined by AnalysisType you have specified. If the AnalysisType's name has a BOOLEAN in it, Analysis will expect boolean values etc. If the Type and return value mismatch, exception is thrown and the result on the analysis page will say that error occurred as the value. If a player has no value a -1 should be returned in the case of a Number. -1 is excluded from the Average calculation's size and total.
        Specified by:
        getValue in class PluginData
        Parameters:
        uuid - UUID of the player the value belongs to.
        Returns:
        Long, Integer, Double, Boolean or String, return -1 if the player has no value.
